<bibRefCitation id="EFE7F4AF8D29FFE7B167FC62FAD4FC1A" author="Anker, A. &amp; De Grave, S." box="[1050,1334,907,934]" pageId="17" pageNumber="206" pagination="343 - 454" refId="ref16773" refString="Anker, A. &amp; De Grave, S. (2016) An updated and annotated checklist of marine and brackish caridean shrimps of Singapore (Crustacea, Decapoda). Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 34, 343 - 454." type="journal article" year="2016">Anker &amp; De Grave 2016</bibRefCitation>
), and the Mediterranean (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE7F4AF8D29FFE7B436FC46FDFBFC75" author="Abdelsalam, K. M." box="[331,537,943,969]" pageId="17" pageNumber="206" pagination="124 - 131" refId="ref16184" refString="Abdelsalam, K. M. (2018) First record of exotic Lysmatid shrimp Lysmata vittata (Stimpson, 1860) (Decapoda: Caridea: Lysmatidae) from the Egyptian Mediterranean coast. Mediterranean Marine Science, 19 (1), 124 - 131. https: // doi. org / 10.12681 / mms. 15591" type="journal article" year="2018">Abdelsalam 2018</bibRefCitation>
). Additionally, both species are likely to tolerate tropical conditions and could overlap in large portions of the Indo-Pacific. Thus, given that 
<taxonomicName id="4C76F2DD8D29FFE7B639FC3AFC4BFC50" baseAuthorityName="Stimpson" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[836,937,979,1004]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="17" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis id="B902554C8D29FFE7B639FC3AFC4BFC50" box="[836,937,979,1004]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="206">L. vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is likely restricted to the temperate/subtropical waters of the northern Indo-Pacific and 
<collectingCountry id="F361C9CE8D29FFE7B7FEFC1EFCFFFBAD" box="[643,797,1015,1041]" name="New Zealand" pageId="17" pageNumber="206">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
, it is difficult to reclassify historic reports of “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C76F2DD8D29FFE7B057FC1EFA72FBAC" baseAuthorityName="Stimpson" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[1322,1424,1015,1040]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="17" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis id="B902554C8D29FFE7B057FC1EFA72FBAC" box="[1322,1424,1015,1040]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="206">L. vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” from the tropical Indo-Pacific as either 
<taxonomicName id="4C76F2DD8D29FFE7B71FFBF2FD5AFB89" authorityName="Laubenheimer &amp; Rhyne" authorityYear="2010" box="[610,696,1051,1077]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="17" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rauli">
<emphasis id="B902554C8D29FFE7B71FFBF2FD5AFB89" box="[610,696,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="206">L. rauli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<emphasis id="B902554C8D29FFE7B799FBF2FD19FB88" box="[740,763,1051,1076]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="206">L.</emphasis>
sp. AUS2. However, natural biogeographic barriers in the region, such as the Sunda Shelf can affect gene flow and aid speciation events (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE7F4AF8D29FFE7B162FBD6FAC6FBE5" author="Briggs, J. C. &amp; Bowen, B. W." box="[1055,1316,1087,1113]" pageId="17" pageNumber="206" pagination="1023 - 1035" refId="ref18494" refString="Briggs, J. C. &amp; Bowen, B. W. (2013) Marine shelf habitat: Biogeography and evolution. Journal of Biogeography, 40 (6), 1023 - 1035. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / jbi. 12082" type="journal article" year="2013">Briggs &amp; Bowen 2013</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE7F4AF8D29FFE7B04CFBD6FF15FBC2" author="Bowen, B. W. &amp; Gaither, M. R. &amp; DiBattista, J. D. &amp; Iacchei, M. &amp; Andrews, K. R. &amp; Grant, W. S. &amp; Toonen, R. J. &amp; Briggs, J. C." pageId="17" pageNumber="206" pagination="7962 - 7969" refId="ref18338" refString="Bowen, B. W., Gaither, M. R., DiBattista, J. D., Iacchei, M., Andrews, K. R., Grant, W. S., Toonen, R. J. &amp; Briggs, J. C. (2016) Comparative phylogeography of the ocean planet. Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences of the United States of America, 113 (29), 7962 - 7969. https: // doi. org / 10.1073 / pnas. 1602404113" type="journal article" year="2016">
Bowen 
<emphasis id="B902554C8D29FFE7B0F5FBD6FF56FBC1" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="206">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
) and may provide insight into the biogeography of 
<taxonomicName id="4C76F2DD8D29FFE7B63BFB8AFC7EFBC1" authorityName="Laubenheimer &amp; Rhyne" authorityYear="2010" box="[838,924,1123,1149]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="17" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rauli">
<emphasis id="B902554C8D29FFE7B63BFB8AFC7EFBC1" box="[838,924,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="206">L. rauli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="B902554C8D29FFE7B6ABFB8AFC0FFBC0" box="[982,1005,1123,1148]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="206">L.</emphasis>
sp. AUS2. A directed sampling effort throughout the wider Indo-Pacific is required to determine the distribution of both species and others once confused with 
<taxonomicName id="4C76F2DD8D29FFE7B5ADFB42FED4FB78" baseAuthorityName="Stimpson" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[208,310,1195,1220]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="17" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis id="B902554C8D29FFE7B5ADFB42FED4FB78" box="[208,310,1195,1220]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="206">L. vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the region.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36CDAD58D29FFE7B5BAFB26FC4BF8CD" pageId="17" pageNumber="206" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BC9895E8D29FFE7B5BAFB26FE18FA7D" blockId="17.[151,1437,618,1905]" pageId="17" pageNumber="206">
Our analyses confirm the occurrence of 
<taxonomicName id="4C76F2DD8D29FFE7B7F4FB26FD3EFB55" authorityName="Laubenheimer &amp; Rhyne" authorityYear="2010" box="[649,732,1231,1257]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="17" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rauli">
<emphasis id="B902554C8D29FFE7B7F4FB26FD3EFB55" box="[649,732,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="206">L. rauli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Panama, Brazil, Thailand, and Hong Kong. We posit that 
<taxonomicName id="4C76F2DD8D29FFE7B0FBFB26FF2FFAB1" authorityName="Laubenheimer &amp; Rhyne" authorityYear="2010" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="17" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rauli">
<emphasis id="B902554C8D29FFE7B0FBFB26FF2FFAB1" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="206">L. rauli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is native to the subtropical and tropical Indo-Pacific and introduced in the western Atlantic, including the 
<typeStatus id="54CD37FC8D29FFE7B011FB1AFA7EFAB1" box="[1388,1436,1267,1293]" pageId="17" pageNumber="206">type</typeStatus>
locality, Salvador, northeastern Brazil. The phylogenetic and geographic affinity between 
<taxonomicName id="4C76F2DD8D29FFE7B1FFFAFEFB37FA8D" authorityName="Laubenheimer &amp; Rhyne" authorityYear="2010" box="[1154,1237,1303,1329]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="17" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rauli">
<emphasis id="B902554C8D29FFE7B1FFFAFEFB37FA8D" box="[1154,1237,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="206">L. rauli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and other species that naturally occur in the Indo-Pacific suggests 
<taxonomicName id="4C76F2DD8D29FFE7B7C9FAD2FCEAFAE9" authorityName="Laubenheimer &amp; Rhyne" authorityYear="2010" box="[692,776,1339,1365]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="17" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rauli">
<emphasis id="B902554C8D29FFE7B7C9FAD2FCEAFAE9" box="[692,776,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="206">L. rauli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is native to this region. We observed in our phylogeny that 
<taxonomicName id="4C76F2DD8D29FFE7B5EAFAB6FF09FAC5" authorityName="Laubenheimer &amp; Rhyne" authorityYear="2010" box="[151,235,1375,1401]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="17" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rauli">
<emphasis id="B902554C8D29FFE7B5EAFAB6FF09FAC5" box="[151,235,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="206">L. rauli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comprised a monophyletic lineage with 
<emphasis id="B902554C8D29FFE7B7C8FAB6FD2EFAC4" box="[693,716,1375,1400]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="206">L.</emphasis>
sp. AUS2 and 
<emphasis id="B902554C8D29FFE7B608FAB6FC6EFAC4" box="[885,908,1375,1400]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="206">L.</emphasis>
sp. 
<collectingCountry id="F361C9CE8D29FFE7B6C7FAB6FBF4FAC5" box="[954,1046,1375,1401]" name="China" pageId="17" pageNumber="206">CHINA</collectingCountry>
, two species from the Indo-Pacific (fig. 4). This clade was sister to a clade that included four other species from the Indo-Pacific (
<taxonomicName id="4C76F2DD8D29FFE7B199FA6AFAAEFA20" baseAuthorityName="Stimpson" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[1252,1356,1411,1436]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="17" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis id="B902554C8D29FFE7B199FA6AFAAEFA20" box="[1252,1356,1411,1436]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="206">L. vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="B902554C8D29FFE7B021FA6AFA91FA20" box="[1372,1395,1411,1436]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="206">L.</emphasis>
sp. AUS1, 
<taxonomicName id="4C76F2DD8D29FFE7B596FA4EFEB3FA7D" box="[235,337,1447,1473]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="17" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dispar">
<emphasis id="B902554C8D29FFE7B596FA4EFEB3FA7D" box="[235,337,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="206">L. dispar</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C76F2DD8D29FFE7B4F3FA4EFE0BFA7D" authorityName="Okuno &amp; Fiedler" authorityYear="2010" box="[398,489,1447,1473]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="17" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lipkei">
<emphasis id="B902554C8D29FFE7B4F3FA4EFE0BFA7D" box="[398,489,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="206">L. lipkei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC9895E8D29FFE7B5BAFA22FC4BF8CD" blockId="17.[151,1437,618,1905]" pageId="17" pageNumber="206">
Similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C76F2DD8D29FFE7B440FA22FE41FA58" baseAuthorityName="Stimpson" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[317,419,1483,1508]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="17" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis id="B902554C8D29FFE7B440FA22FE41FA58" box="[317,419,1483,1508]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="206">L. vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the western Atlantic, we assume ballast water was the introduction vector for 
<taxonomicName id="4C76F2DD8D29FFE7B056FA22FA9DFA59" authorityName="Laubenheimer &amp; Rhyne" authorityYear="2010" box="[1323,1407,1483,1509]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="17" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rauli">
<emphasis id="B902554C8D29FFE7B056FA22FA9DFA59" box="[1323,1407,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="206">L. rauli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry id="F361C9CE8D29FFE7B5EAFA06FF3DF9B5" box="[151,223,1519,1545]" name="Brazil" pageId="17" pageNumber="206">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. To date, 
<taxonomicName id="4C76F2DD8D29FFE7B431FA06FE42F9B5" authorityName="Laubenheimer &amp; Rhyne" authorityYear="2010" box="[332,416,1519,1545]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="17" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rauli">
<emphasis id="B902554C8D29FFE7B431FA06FE42F9B5" box="[332,416,1519,1545]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="206">L. rauli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been reported along a large swath of Brazilian coastline, from Ilha de Anhatomirim in the south to the Vaza-Barris estuary in the north (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE7F4AF8D29FFE7B7C8F9FAFC94F991" author="Alves, D. F. R. &amp; Lima, D. J. M. &amp; Hirose, G. L. &amp; Martinez, P. A. &amp; Dolabella, S. S. &amp; Barros-Alves, S. P." box="[693,886,1555,1581]" pageId="17" pageNumber="206" pagination="41 - 55" refId="ref16601" refString="Alves, D. F. R., Lima, D. J. M., Hirose, G. L., Martinez, P. A., Dolabella, S. S. &amp; Barros-Alves, S. P. (2018) Morphological and molecular analyses confirm the occurrence of two sympatric Lysmata shrimp (Crustacea, Decapoda) in the southwestern Atlantic. Zootaxa, 4526 (1), 41 - 55. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4526.1.3" type="journal article" year="2018">
Alves 
<emphasis id="B902554C8D29FFE7B783F9FAFCD7F991" box="[766,821,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="206">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE7F4AF8D29FFE7B6FCF9FAFBBCF991" author="Pachelle, P. P. G. &amp; Leray, M. &amp; Anker, A. &amp; Lasley, R." box="[897,1118,1555,1581]" pageId="17" pageNumber="206" pagination="128 - 136" refId="ref22223" refString="Pachelle, P. P. G., Leray, M., Anker, A. &amp; Lasley, R. (2018) Five new records of marine shrimps (Decapoda: Caridea, Stenopodidea) from the Caribbean coast of Panama. Zootaxa, 4438 (1), 128 - 136. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4438.1.5" type="journal article" year="2018">
Pachelle 
<emphasis id="B902554C8D29FFE7B69BF9FAFBFCF991" box="[998,1054,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="206">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
, 2020; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE7F4AF8D29FFE7B1D2F9FAFA9BF991" author="Santos, R. de &amp; Alves, D. F. R. &amp; Carvalho-Batista, A." box="[1199,1401,1555,1581]" pageId="17" pageNumber="206" pagination="1 - 13" refId="ref23026" refString="Santos, R. de C., Alves, D. F. R. &amp; Carvalho-Batista, A. (2021) Shrimps of genus Lysmata Risso, 1816 (Caridea: Lysmatidae) from Queimada Grande Island region, southeastern Brazil. Nauplius, 29, 1 - 13. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / 2358 - 2936 e 2021032" type="journal article" year="2021">
Santos 
<emphasis id="B902554C8D29FFE7B182F9FAFAD5F991" box="[1279,1335,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="206">et al.</emphasis>
2021
</bibRefCitation>
). It is uncertain if the Panamanian populations resulted from separate introduction events or if shrimp moved northward naturally from 
<collectingCountry id="F361C9CE8D29FFE7B442F9B2FE65F9C9" box="[319,391,1627,1653]" name="Brazil" pageId="17" pageNumber="206">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE7F4AF8D29FFE7B4ECF9B2FD9DF9C9" author="Pachelle, P. P. G. &amp; Leray, M. &amp; Anker, A. &amp; Lasley, R." box="[401,639,1627,1653]" pageId="17" pageNumber="206" pagination="128 - 136" refId="ref22223" refString="Pachelle, P. P. G., Leray, M., Anker, A. &amp; Lasley, R. (2018) Five new records of marine shrimps (Decapoda: Caridea, Stenopodidea) from the Caribbean coast of Panama. Zootaxa, 4438 (1), 128 - 136. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4438.1.5" type="journal article" year="2018">
Pachelle 
<emphasis id="B902554C8D29FFE7B48BF9B2FDCCF9C9" box="[502,558,1627,1653]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="206">et al.</emphasis>
(2018)
</bibRefCitation>
surmised the introduction of 
<taxonomicName id="4C76F2DD8D29FFE7B6B5F9B2FBFEF9C9" authorityName="Laubenheimer &amp; Rhyne" authorityYear="2010" box="[968,1052,1627,1653]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="17" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rauli">
<emphasis id="B902554C8D29FFE7B6B5F9B2FBFEF9C9" box="[968,1052,1627,1653]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="206">L. rauli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(cited as 
<taxonomicName id="4C76F2DD8D29FFE7B1FAF9B2FB0FF9C8" baseAuthorityName="Stimpson" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[1159,1261,1627,1652]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="17" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis id="B902554C8D29FFE7B1FAF9B2FB0FF9C8" box="[1159,1261,1627,1652]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="206">L. vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) in the Western Atlantic resulted from a recent and very quick invasion. Reinforcing this hypothesis are the introductions of other Asian decapod crustaceans within 
<collectingCountry id="F361C9CE8D29FFE7B760F94AFD86F901" box="[541,612,1699,1725]" name="Brazil" pageId="17" pageNumber="206">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, including another lysmatid shrimp, 
<taxonomicName id="4C76F2DD8D29FFE7B17CF94AFBBFF901" authorityName="Okuno &amp; Fiedler" authorityYear="2010" box="[1025,1117,1699,1725]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="17" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lipkei">
<emphasis id="B902554C8D29FFE7B17CF94AFBBFF901" box="[1025,1117,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="206">L. lipkei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE7F4AF8D29FFE7B110F94AFAB3F901" author="Pachelle, P. P. G. &amp; Anker, A. &amp; Mendes, C. B. &amp; Bezerra, L. E. A." box="[1133,1361,1699,1725]" pageId="17" pageNumber="206" pagination="1 - 63" refId="ref22143" refString="Pachelle, P. P. G., Anker, A., Mendes, C. B. &amp; Bezerra, L. E. A. (2016) Decapod crustaceans from the state of Ceara, northeastern Brazil: an updated checklist of marine and estuarine species, with 23 new records. Zootaxa, 4131 (1), 1 - 63. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4131.1.1" type="journal article" year="2016">
Pachelle 
<emphasis id="B902554C8D29FFE7B1A8F94AFAECF901" box="[1237,1294,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="206">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE7F4AF8D29FFE7B026F94AFEF4F95D" author="Alves, D. F. R. &amp; Lima, D. J. M. &amp; Hirose, G. L. &amp; Martinez, P. A. &amp; Dolabella, S. S. &amp; Barros-Alves, S. P." pageId="17" pageNumber="206" pagination="41 - 55" refId="ref16601" refString="Alves, D. F. R., Lima, D. J. M., Hirose, G. L., Martinez, P. A., Dolabella, S. S. &amp; Barros-Alves, S. P. (2018) Morphological and molecular analyses confirm the occurrence of two sympatric Lysmata shrimp (Crustacea, Decapoda) in the southwestern Atlantic. Zootaxa, 4526 (1), 41 - 55. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4526.1.3" type="journal article" year="2018">
Alves 
<emphasis id="B902554C8D29FFE7B5EAF92EFF33F95D" box="[151,209,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="206">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
), the alpheid shrimp 
<taxonomicName id="4C76F2DD8D29FFE7B77AF92EFC71F95D" authority="Ortmann 1894" authorityName="Ortmann" authorityYear="1894" box="[519,915,1735,1761]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Athanas" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="17" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dimorphus">
